decision_conditions:
Condition : 18 - Prior to the commencement of development, details must be submitted to and approved in writring by the Local Authority which show the following flood risk mitigation measures. 

-The use of a continuous secant pile wall around the entire development or suitable alternative, which reduces the risk of internal flooding; 
-Basement to be fully waterproofed (tanked) 
-Wall sockets to be raised to as high as is practicable and sockets fed from the ceiling down in order to minimise damage if flood waters inundate the property and air bricks to be raised.
-The installation of a basement dewatering system and a positive pump device to prevent any back-flow from the sewerage network; 
-The inclusion of a minimum of +300mm freeboard above the top of the basement wall to ensure protection above the design flood level (to be agreed with the Local Authority) in the event of a blockage of the adjoining allotment ditch; 
-Provision of cross sections through the basement and adjoining allotment land showing detailed design with topographic levels to mAOD showing the required standard of protection against flooding.

The mitigation measures must be implemented during construction of the development and completed prior to the occupation of the proposed development.

Reason: To reduce the impact the site may experience as a result of fluvial flooding and or surface water flooding to the proposed development and future users, in accordance with Merton's policies CS16, DMF2 and the London Plan policy SI 13
